 <text>
  <front>
   <head>Transcrib'd from the Rev. Mr. PIXEL'S Parsonage Garden near BIRMINGHAM, 1757.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">SEEK not in these  to view</l>
     <l n="2" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Dryads green, or Naiads blue;</l>
     <l n="3" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Such as haunt, at eve or dawn,</l>
     <l n="4" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">lake, or  lawn:</l>
     <l n="5" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Such as sport on  meads;</l>
     <l n="6" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Such as  Genius leads</l>
     <l n="7" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">O'er vale and hill, and to their care</l>
     <l n="8" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Consigns his waves and woodlands fair;</l>
     <l n="9" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">While the Muses vacant stray,</l>
     <l n="10" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">And Echo wants her sweetest lay.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="11" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Long, long may those unrival'd shine,</l>
     <l n="12" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Nor shall my temp'rate breast repine,</l>
     <l n="13" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">So Music lend her willing aid</l>
     <l n="14" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">To gladden this ignoble shade;</l>
     <l n="15" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">So Peace endear this humble plain â€”</l>
     <l n="16" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">And haply Elegance will deign</l>
     <l n="17" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">To wander here, and smiling see</l>
     <l n="18" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Her sister nymph Simplicity.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
